 Renaissance.  Weaving this revolution against a backdrop of historic Mexican American activism from the 1930s to the 1960s and the contemporary black power and black civil rights movements, García gives readers the best representations of the Chicano generation in Los Angeles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChicano movementxCaliforniaxLos AngelesxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aChicano movementzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z978311062111240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096136440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961364423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961364/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles